          <change when="2013-06-13T06:13:03.195-04:00"
                 who="https://papyri.info/editor/users/simoeis">Concerning line 6 of this papyrus, Jane Rowlandson writes in an email dated 15.04.13: "BGU 2.487 should be expanded κατοικ(ικὰς) with arouras, not κάτοικ(ος) with Theano." Rowlandson argues that a land category is always required before ἄρουραι.  She also notes that this text is not included in Canducci’s (1990, 1991) list of the 6475 Arsinoite Hellenes/katoikoi and adds that Canducci "evidently already realised the correct interpretation."</change>
          <change when="2013-06-13T06:13:02-04:00" who="https://papyri.info/editor/users/simoeis">Submit - Concerning line 6 of this papyrus, Jane Rowlandson writes in an email dated 15.04.13: "BGU 2.487 should be expanded κατοικ(ικὰς) with arouras, not κάτοικ(ος) with Theano." Rowlandson argues that a land category is always required before ἄρουραι.  She also notes that this text is not included in Canducci’s (1990, 1991) list of the 6475 Arsinoite Hellenes/katoikoi and adds that Canducci "evidently already realised the correct interpretation."</change>
